{
  "text": "The heat release distribution for jet-wake stabilized combustion is mostly consistent with the lifted diffusion flame description proposed in Ref. [CITATION_1] . The initial peak in OH* (or CH*) signal corresponds to the premixed flame base where the fuel that has premixed with air in the lift-off distance is consumed. After the end of the premixed flame base, the combustion is mixing limited. These regions are illustrated in Fig. 23 . Recent PLIF imaging in the combustor suggests a rich premixed flame cone exists inside flame base along the jet-perimeter.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "95765535"
